US — Create a new ServiceNow Request when no matching restitution request exists

As a system
I want to create a new ServiceNow Request when no matching restitution request exists
So that the hardware return is properly tracked in the Group process

Description

When a hardware return is completed and:
	•	RequestAllowed = true
	•	no existing open restitution request is found for the identified user and equipment type

the application must:
	1.	Create a new ServiceNow Request
	•	using the correct offering Sys ID
	•	passing all required variables in the request creation endpoint
	2.	Resolve and populate the required Sys IDs
	•	requested_for: resolve the ServiceNow Sys ID of the visitor / initiator
	•	var_uid_supplier: resolve the ServiceNow Sys ID corresponding to the supplier identity
	•	var_uid_recipient: resolve the ServiceNow Sys ID corresponding to the recipient identity
	•	var_stockroom: resolve the Sys ID of the stockroom where the return took place
	•	var_equipment: resolve the Sys ID of the returned equipment
	3.	Populate the functional variables
Including at minimum:
	•	request type
	•	material type
	•	battery charger returned
	•	restitution location / stockroom label
	•	accessories returned
	•	PV file name
	•	PV file location
	•	signed minutes / signature status
	•	comments
	4.	Handle the generated downstream records
Once the Request is created and generates:
	•	an RITM
	•	a SCTask / SVTask
the application must update the generated task through the appropriate API endpoint in order to:
	•	set the assignment group to the comptoir where the return occurred
	•	assign the technician in charge
	•	set the task to the expected resolved/completed state

